venue.name: Paramus Park Mall

formattedAddress: 700 Paramus Park (btwn Route 17 & Garden State Pkwy)

venue.header: According to the Foursquare community, this place is a 7.4 out of 10.
venue.explanation: We take into account visits and input from our community. You'll see a number on places based off of ratings and tips written by people like you.

items.summary: Lots of people like this place

venue.description: Welcome to Paramus Park, where you’ll discover more than 100 specialty shops and your favorite department stores filled with everything on your list. Bring the kids and take a load off at the children’s play area, then grab a bite at one of the popular quick-serve or full service restaurants.

pageInfo.description: GGP is a fully integrated, self-managed real estate investment trust focused on owning, managing, leasing, and redeveloping high-quality shopping malls.

items.text: I like this mall because my go-to shops are here! Also, I'm 24 not 14. I want to get in & out without dodging packs of slow-moving high schoolers trying to make friends with "cute" strangers.
come here if you dont wanna deal with GSP
Very low key, no obnoxious people.
The food court is way better than the one at Garden State Plaza

items.name: New Jersey Shopping Malls
items.description: New Jersey has more malls per square mile than any other state. This list is sorted (as best as possible), from the biggest malls to smallest. Now you know the best places to shop.

tip.text: It's a nice mall that isn't overcrowded.
